1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
 (upbeat music)

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:25,000
 - All right, well, hello porch.

3
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,560
 Good to see you.

4
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:28,360
 What a gift to be here.

5
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:30,440
 Thanks Kylan, I have been encouraged

6
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:33,900
 by the ministry of the porch for a very, very long time.

7
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:37,360
 So it's a bit surreal for me to get to be here.

8
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:39,280
 I know you're here all the time.

9
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:41,240
 I'm sure you know how amazing it is

10
00:00:41,240 --> 00:00:42,300
 that you get to be a part of this,

11
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:45,040
 but what God is doing in and through this ministry

12
00:00:45,040 --> 00:00:46,160
 is incredible.

13
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:49,560
 So from Atlanta to you, thank you.

14
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:51,000
 And thanks for having me here tonight.

15
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,040
 Kylan, thanks for having me.

16
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:54,280
 I love listening to Kylan preach.

17
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:55,840
 I love listening to TA preach.

18
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:57,960
 It's not really fair that they're at the same church,

19
00:00:57,960 --> 00:01:00,680
 but it's a real gift to be here.

20
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:02,840
 And I'm so excited about the message.

21
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:05,920
 I believe the Lord's given me for us tonight.

22
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,600
 I wanna introduce you just a little bit.

23
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:09,700
 I know you don't need to know everything about me,

24
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:12,040
 but just a little bit since it's my first time here.

25
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:13,600
 This is a picture of my family.

26
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:17,760
 My wife and I have been married for just over 10 years.

27
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:20,040
 And these are our three girls.

28
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:22,560
 The oldest on the bottom left is Mercy.

29
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:27,880
 The blonde is Ember and Charlie is our baby.

30
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:29,920
 Mercy is a typical firstborn.

31
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:31,760
 She asks for extra homework

32
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:34,480
 and has never broken a rule in her life.

33
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:37,340
 Ember, we're not sure if she's gonna run

34
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:40,560
 a very large company one day or be incarcerated.

35
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:41,400
 Time will tell.

36
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,220
 (congregation laughing)

37
00:01:42,220 --> 00:01:45,000
 And then Charlie is just happy to be alive.

38
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,880
 You know, third kid, never had a bad day in her life,

39
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:52,880
 but it's crazy how much joy they bring to my life.

40
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,960
 So love them a lot.

41
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:57,640
 I'm a part of Passion City Church in Atlanta, Georgia.

42
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:59,240
 Been on team there for over 12 years,

43
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:02,240
 currently serving as the teaching pastor.

44
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:05,640
 And I'm so grateful that the Lord has invited me

45
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:07,200
 into what he's doing.

46
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,500
 So it's not the message tonight,

47
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,680
 but if I can just put a message before the message,

48
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:14,080
 the message would be God's plans for your life

49
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:17,120
 are so much better than your plans for your life.

50
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,640
 And I hope you believe that to be true.

51
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:22,600
 I've loved journeying along these last few weeks.

52
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,440
 It had been amazing.

53
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:27,560
 As you've been talking about mental health and health

54
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:29,240
 and perspective and navigating all that.

55
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:32,000
 And as I felt what the Lord was putting on my heart

56
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,480
 to share tonight, it was kind of beautiful

57
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,320
 how I think these things belong together

58
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:40,000
 because the title of the message tonight

59
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,600
 is you should get your hopes up.

60
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:45,160
 Can you just tell your neighbor that?

61
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:47,360
 Tell him, say, you should get your hopes up.

62
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:50,760
 And here's what I want you to understand.

63
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:53,800
 And I believe this with all of my heart.

64
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:58,680
 I believe that our health and our hope

65
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:02,000
 are inextricably linked together.

66
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,280
 That our health and our hope

67
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:06,560
 are part of the same conversation.

68
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:07,920
 Maybe you've heard it said before,

69
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:10,060
 you can go 40 days without food.

70
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:12,620
 That's pretty wild.

71
00:03:12,620 --> 00:03:13,560
 I don't know if I really could or not,

72
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,840
 but apparently you can.

73
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:17,920
 You can go four days without water.

74
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:21,060
 You can go four minutes without air,

75
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:24,660
 but you can't go four seconds without hope.

76
00:03:24,660 --> 00:03:26,260
 And I know when we talk about hope,

77
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:29,540
 there's immediately this thing that happens in us.

78
00:03:29,540 --> 00:03:33,620
 Some of us chalk hope up to this ethereal,

79
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:37,740
 touchy, feely, belongs on a self-help aisle

80
00:03:37,740 --> 00:03:38,680
 of the bookstore.

81
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:41,180
 But what I'm hoping the Lord will open our eyes

82
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:44,860
 to see today is hope is what we have as the people of God.

83
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:47,700
 Hope is not just blind optimism.

84
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,460
 It is gritty theology.

85
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:53,020
 We are meant to display to the world

86
00:03:53,020 --> 00:03:56,940
 a sure and confident hope.

87
00:03:56,940 --> 00:04:01,940
 And so if we are people who belong to the God of hope,

88
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:05,500
 then we should get our hopes up.

89
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,980
 You should get your hopes up.

90
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:09,460
 I don't know how your hope is doing right now.

91
00:04:09,460 --> 00:04:11,060
 I don't know if you feel hopeful

92
00:04:11,060 --> 00:04:14,220
 and you feel confident about what the future holds for you.

93
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:16,940
 I don't know if you've got all kinds of,

94
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:19,120
 you know, like fog in front of you

95
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,100
 and you're going, I don't know, man.

96
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:22,340
 I don't know if what's in front of me is good or not.

97
00:04:22,340 --> 00:04:25,920
 I want to say to you on the authority of God's word today,

98
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:29,500
 not a self-help message, but from his word today,

99
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:32,920
 you should get your hopes up.

100
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:35,940
 God has great things in store for you.

101
00:04:35,940 --> 00:04:39,300
 He has given great purpose to your life

102
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:40,980
 and his plans for you are good.

103
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:42,380
 Do you believe that?

104
00:04:42,380 --> 00:04:44,540
 I'm not saying they're gonna be easy.

105
00:04:44,540 --> 00:04:45,820
 I'm not saying they're gonna be comfortable.

106
00:04:45,820 --> 00:04:47,260
 I'm not saying you're gonna get the internship

107
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:48,780
 and you're gonna get the job and you're gonna get the girl

108
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:49,620
 and you're gonna get everything.

109
00:04:49,620 --> 00:04:50,440
 That's not what I'm saying.

110
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:51,760
 I'm saying they're good.

111
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:54,020
 His plans for you are good.

112
00:04:54,020 --> 00:04:56,240
 Do you believe that?

113
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,660
 And as the people of God,

114
00:04:57,660 --> 00:05:00,920
 we are meant to live with this expectation

115
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:04,640
 and eagerness and anticipation

116
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:06,280
 that as I survey the landscape

117
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:09,720
 or even as I look at my own life, oftentimes I don't have.

118
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:16,840
 Have you ever gotten your hopes up only to be disappointed?

119
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,380
 That's not a good feeling, is it?

120
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:23,000
 Yesterday, this is kind of crazy,

121
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,820
 in Atlanta, Georgia, it was snowing.

122
00:05:24,820 --> 00:05:27,680
 Look it up.

123
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,640
 You all think I'm lying.

124
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:29,480
 Look it up.

125
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,300
 It was snowing.

126
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:31,200
 Now I'm not talking about like we were sledding,

127
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,360
 but I'm saying there was snow that came down from the sky

128
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,480
 yesterday in Atlanta, Georgia.

129
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:37,320
 And when we picked our kids up from school,

130
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:39,560
 there was like snow flurries happening

131
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:42,760
 and they had all the plans.

132
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:44,360
 We're gonna cancel school tomorrow.

133
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:46,120
 We're gonna go sledding.

134
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:48,240
 We're gonna do all the stuff we've seen in all the movies

135
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,760
 and growing up in Atlanta, Georgia,

136
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:52,280
 probably similar if you grew up in Dallas, Texas,

137
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:55,280
 the idea of snow is a constant topic

138
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:59,320
 of getting your hopes up only to be disappointed.

139
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:00,920
 You're gonna go to school tomorrow

140
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,560
 and you ain't gonna be able to sled

141
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:06,240
 'cause you live in Dallas, Texas or Atlanta, Georgia.

142
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,060
 But it's a hard thing.

143
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,240
 I remember this summer,

144
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:11,600
 the girls were wanting to go to the pool constantly,

145
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,160
 and we had a month where it felt like

146
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,520
 it rained every single day.

147
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:16,920
 And we'd be at the dinner table and they would say to me,

148
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,600
 like, "Daddy, can we please go to the pool tomorrow?

149
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,000
 "Can we please go to the pool tomorrow?"

150
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,600
 And I was kind of like conflicted

151
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,320
 because I wanted to say to them,

152
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:25,120
 "Of course we can go to the pool tomorrow."

153
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,640
 But I also knew that the forecast

154
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,480
 was like 100% chance of rain.

155
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,600
 And so I would just like trying to be a good dad.

156
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:33,280
 I'm like, "Yeah, we can go to the pool tomorrow."

157
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:35,120
 And then the next morning at breakfast,

158
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:38,640
 I'm having breakfast with two girls in Moana bathing suits

159
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:41,040
 and they're just ready to go to the pool.

160
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,480
 And it's pouring down rain outside

161
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:45,680
 and I just would watch their faces kind of collapse.

162
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:49,680
 It's not a fun thing to get your hopes up

163
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:52,000
 only to be disappointed.

164
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,600
 Maybe it's something like a sports team

165
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,960
 that you thought was gonna be good

166
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:58,680
 and then they were like they always were.

167
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:02,160
 Or maybe it was college application.

168
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:04,200
 You thought you were gonna get into a certain school,

169
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,440
 you had a plan for your life,

170
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,000
 but instead of an acceptance letter,

171
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,160
 you got a rejection letter and your hopes got up

172
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,600
 and then you got crushed.

173
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:14,760
 Maybe you experienced with a relationship.

174
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:16,000
 Somebody that told you one thing

175
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,200
 and then did a different thing.

176
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,400
 Maybe you experienced with a parent,

177
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,000
 somebody who committed to your family

178
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,200
 and you thought they would always be there

179
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,280
 and then all of a sudden they just up and left

180
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:28,340
 and you got your hopes up for what life would be like

181
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:31,240
 only to be disappointed and crushed.

182
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:33,480
 Or maybe for you it was a career.

183
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:35,360
 For me, I spent 20 years of my life

184
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:37,080
 thinking I was gonna do one thing with my life,

185
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:38,400
 play a game for the rest of my life

186
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,260
 only for injury to come and a doctor to tell me

187
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:41,480
 I could never play the game again.

188
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:44,360
 And my hopes were up and in 30 seconds,

189
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,600
 they came crashing down.

190
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:49,800
 I remember when my wife and I were buying our first house.

191
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,760
 This is not a fun process.

192
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:54,400
 It's less fun now 'cause the interest rates are like 10%,

193
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:56,680
 but it wasn't fun when I bought a house either.

194
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,720
 And I can remember we went to the first house

195
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,800
 with our real estate agent and we walked in

196
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,680
 and it was amazing.

197
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:06,800
 I mean, it was tiny, it was like 800 square feet.

198
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,620
 And we walked in and it looked like Chip and Joanna

199
00:08:09,620 --> 00:08:10,560
 had just been there.

200
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:13,000
 There was shiplap everywhere, like on every wall,

201
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,560
 and we're walking around and my newlywed wife and me,

202
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:17,400
 and we're like, "This is what this room's gonna be.

203
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,160
 "And this is what this room's gonna be."

204
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:21,840
 And that's like all the rooms, and it's gonna be awesome.

205
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:23,900
 And we went out and I'm not kidding you,

206
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:25,040
 I have a picture on my phone.

207
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:27,280
 We went out into the driveway, we held hands,

208
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:29,240
 and we were like, "This is gonna be so amazing."

209
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:32,040
 And in our minds, we had already moved into the house.

210
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:34,740
 And let me just pre-warn you,

211
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:36,880
 if you haven't bought a house yet,

212
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:39,680
 you ain't gonna get the first house you look at.

213
00:08:39,680 --> 00:08:42,680
 Because our real estate agent called us a few hours later

214
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:46,720
 and said, "Hey, somebody paid all cash for the house

215
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:51,000
 "and they bought it at $100,000 over asking price."

216
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:53,540
 And I was like, "Who are all these rich jokers

217
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:55,940
 "with $100,000 cash?"

218
00:08:55,940 --> 00:09:00,040
 And we went into the next house.

219
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:01,160
 And our hopes were high,

220
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,560
 but not as high as the first house.

221
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:05,800
 And then we went into the next one and didn't get it.

222
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:08,040
 And then we went into the next one and didn't get it.

223
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:10,440
 And then we went into the next one and didn't get it.

224
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:13,680
 And every single time we walked into a new house,

225
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:17,360
 even if we loved the house,

226
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:21,540
 as a way of protecting ourselves from disappointment,

227
00:09:21,540 --> 00:09:24,640
 we refused to get our hopes up.

228
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:31,720
 And I am convinced there are many of us in this room

229
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,280
 who are living life like that.

230
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:37,520
 Somehow, at some turn in life,

231
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:41,000
 you got your hopes up and you got disappointed.

232
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,560
 And as a way of self-preservation,

233
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:47,080
 as a way of not having to navigate

234
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,880
 through the storms of life,

235
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:52,200
 you've just refused to allow your hopes

236
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,380
 to get up for anything.

237
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:57,880
 But God has a different plan for your life.

238
00:09:57,880 --> 00:09:59,960
 As people who belong to Christ,

239
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,800
 as people who are bought by His blood,

240
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,160
 as people who belong as sons and daughters

241
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:05,280
 of the God of hope,

242
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:10,140
 we are meant to live with confident expectation.

243
00:10:10,140 --> 00:10:15,200
 So I came to Dallas tonight to ask you a simple question.

244
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,360
 How's your hope?

245
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:20,520
 How's your hope?

246
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:23,680
 And for those of you that are barely hanging on today,

247
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,480
 the writer of Hebrews tells us

248
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:29,480
 that we can have an unshakable hope

249
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:34,480
 as an anchor for your soul, firm and secure.

250
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,080
 That's Hebrews chapter six.

251
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:38,480
 What would it look like in your life

252
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:42,080
 if you had a hope that was firm and secure?

253
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,680
 Not fragile, but firm.

254
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:50,500
 Not shifting based on the circumstances of life,

255
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:54,560
 but secure based on the fact that you belong

256
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:56,520
 to the King of Kings.

257
00:10:56,520 --> 00:10:58,640
 And what I wanna do for a few minutes

258
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:01,080
 is look at Romans chapter 15.

259
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:03,160
 We're gonna read 13 verses,

260
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:05,360
 but we're gonna spend almost our entire time

261
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:07,480
 in just one verse.

262
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:11,400
 The last verse, the benediction of Romans chapter 15.

263
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,040
 This is a section that Charles Spurgeon

264
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:14,960
 called one of the richest passages

265
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:17,200
 in the entire word of God.

266
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,240
 So if you have your Bible,

267
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:21,120
 I invite you to turn to Romans chapter 15.

268
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:24,240
 I'm gonna begin reading in verse one.

269
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:26,080
 I think it's important that we see the context.

270
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:30,600
 That's why we're gonna read the first few verses together.

271
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,920
 It says, "We who are strong ought to bear

272
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:34,840
 "with the failings of the weak

273
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:37,280
 "and not to please ourselves.

274
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:40,780
 "Each of us should please our neighbors for their good,

275
00:11:40,780 --> 00:11:42,360
 "to build them up.

276
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:45,060
 "For even Christ did not please himself,

277
00:11:45,060 --> 00:11:46,480
 "but as it is written,

278
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:51,440
 "the insults of those who insult you have fallen on me."

279
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:53,720
 Verse four would be a great verse for you to underline.

280
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:54,820
 We'll come back to this.

281
00:11:54,820 --> 00:11:58,320
 "For everything that was written in the past

282
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:00,420
 "was written to teach us,

283
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:04,780
 "so that through the endurance taught in the scriptures

284
00:12:04,780 --> 00:12:07,620
 "and the encouragement that they provide,

285
00:12:07,620 --> 00:12:10,260
 "we might have,"

286
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:11,660
 can you say the word with me?

287
00:12:11,660 --> 00:12:12,820
 - Hope.

288
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:15,480
 - Okay, that was great, kinda.

289
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:20,020
 If we read the word hope, let's all say it together.

290
00:12:20,020 --> 00:12:23,500
 "Encouragement they provide, we might have."

291
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:24,800
 - Hope. - Hope.

292
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:28,660
 "May the God who gives endurance and encouragement

293
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:31,140
 "give you the same attitude of mind towards each other

294
00:12:31,140 --> 00:12:32,480
 "that Christ Jesus had,

295
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:35,080
 "so that with one mind and one voice,

296
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:37,260
 "you may glorify the God and Father

297
00:12:37,260 --> 00:12:38,720
 "of our Lord Jesus Christ.

298
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,360
 "Accept one another then,

299
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:42,140
 "just as Christ has accepted you,

300
00:12:42,140 --> 00:12:44,460
 "in order to bring praise to God.

301
00:12:44,460 --> 00:12:46,560
 "For I tell you that Christ has become a servant

302
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:48,620
 "of the Jews on behalf of God's truth,

303
00:12:48,620 --> 00:12:50,900
 "so that the promises made to the patriarchs

304
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:51,840
 "might be confirmed,

305
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,960
 "and moreover, that the Gentiles

306
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:57,140
 "might glorify God for his mercy, as it is written.

307
00:12:57,140 --> 00:12:59,820
 "Therefore, I will praise you among the Gentiles,

308
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:02,340
 "I will sing the praises of your name."

309
00:13:02,340 --> 00:13:03,940
 Verse 10, again it says,

310
00:13:03,940 --> 00:13:06,500
 "Rejoice you Gentiles with his people."

311
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,740
 Verse 11, and again,

312
00:13:07,740 --> 00:13:09,680
 "Praise the Lord, all you Gentiles,

313
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:12,460
 "let all the peoples extol him."

314
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:14,500
 And again, Isaiah says,

315
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:18,160
 "The root of Jesse will spring up,

316
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:21,720
 "and one who will arise to rule over the nations,

317
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:26,720
 "in him, the Gentiles will hope."

318
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,000
 Hope.

319
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:30,040
 Verse 13, pay attention closely,

320
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:32,720
 this is our verse for the rest of our time together.

321
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:37,720
 "May the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace,

322
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:40,300
 "as you trust in him,

323
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:44,080
 "so that you may overflow with hope

324
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:49,080
 "by the power of the Holy Spirit, amen."

325
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:52,480
 What a verse.

326
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,400
 Look at that verse.

327
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:56,960
 May the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace,

328
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,320
 as you trust in him,

329
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:01,640
 so that you may overflow with hope

330
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:03,960
 by the power of the Holy Spirit.

331
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:06,000
 Or the ESV translates it this way,

332
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,720
 may the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace

333
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:11,860
 in believing, so that by the power of the Spirit,

334
00:14:11,860 --> 00:14:15,560
 you may abound in hope.

335
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:18,400
 This is really like the exclamation point

336
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:21,080
 at the end of 15 chapters

337
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:23,640
 of brilliant doctrine from Paul.

338
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:26,080
 It's really the end of his teaching in Romans.

339
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:29,080
 After this, you pretty much just have a few final remarks

340
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:31,100
 and final greetings to a few people.

341
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:34,080
 So the crescendo of the book of Romans

342
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:36,040
 ends with this exclamation point,

343
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:40,640
 that we should, as people who belong to the King,

344
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:45,640
 live lives that overflow with hope.

345
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:47,280
 I want you to see a few things.

346
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:49,480
 Number one, if you're taking notes, write this down.

347
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:53,940
 God is the only true source of hope.

348
00:14:53,940 --> 00:14:56,300
 And you see it in the text.

349
00:14:56,300 --> 00:15:00,480
 Paul says here, the God of hope.

350
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:03,360
 So maybe it would be helpful to try and define hope.

351
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:06,400
 Webster defines hope as a desire accompanied

352
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:11,100
 by expectation of or belief in its fulfillment.

353
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:15,400
 It is to want something to happen.

354
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:17,560
 That's how Webster defines hope.

355
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:19,640
 But for the believer, can I encourage you,

356
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:22,840
 hoping is not wishing.

357
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:26,760
 Biblical hope is way more than a simple wish.

358
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:30,660
 It entails certainty based on God's demonstration

359
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:32,280
 of faithfulness in the past

360
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:36,400
 and confidence that he will be faithful in the future.

361
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:40,200
 Our hope as believers is not blind optimism.

362
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:43,240
 It is calculated faith, right?

363
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:46,000
 Optimism is psychological.

364
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:49,560
 Biblical hope is theological.

365
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:52,480
 Optimism counts up the odds.

366
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:57,480
 Biblical hope counts on and in the God of hope.

367
00:15:57,480 --> 00:16:01,320
 I love how John Piper says this.

368
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:05,080
 He says, "Biblical hope is biblical faith

369
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:07,280
 in the future tense."

370
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:08,600
 Don't you love that?

371
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:13,600
 Hope is the result of trusting in God.

372
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:17,060
 So Paul says, "May the God of hope."

373
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:19,660
 Now, this doesn't mean God of hope

374
00:16:19,660 --> 00:16:23,520
 like that he's a God that has hope for the future.

375
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:25,060
 I have a hopeful God.

376
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:26,760
 That's not what Paul's saying.

377
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,600
 God's omniscient.

378
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,260
 He knows how everything's gonna work out tomorrow

379
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:31,800
 and the next day and the next day and the next day

380
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:32,640
 and the next day.

381
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:33,600
 He's never been surprised.

382
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,840
 He's never Googled anything.

383
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,440
 He's never been informed of anything.

384
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:37,400
 He knows everything.

385
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,200
 It's a prerequisite for being God.

386
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:42,480
 So he doesn't have to be hopeful for tomorrow

387
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:43,560
 'cause he's God.

388
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:45,760
 So it's not that he's a hopeful God.

389
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:47,900
 So what's Paul trying to say here?

390
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:51,200
 Well, it says that he's the God of hope.

391
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,760
 And I know many of you won't care about this,

392
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:54,220
 but when I was in seminary,

393
00:16:54,220 --> 00:16:58,040
 we were taught that this is a genitive of product.

394
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:00,800
 That does something for any of the nerds in the room today.

395
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:02,160
 And in seminary, what I was taught,

396
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:04,620
 the best way to understand a generative of product

397
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:08,400
 is to put which or who produces in its place.

398
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,480
 And when you do that,

399
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:11,160
 this starts to make a little bit of sense.

400
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:16,160
 So may the God who produces hope, do you see it?

401
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:17,840
 He's the source.

402
00:17:17,840 --> 00:17:20,240
 He is the only true source.

403
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,680
 He produces hope.

404
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,960
 He is the fountain of hope.

405
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:26,160
 This is our God.

406
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:32,560
 And yet, all throughout the pages of this book

407
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:35,360
 and all throughout the years of your life

408
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:37,840
 and all throughout the years of my life,

409
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:42,840
 we have looked to a million other sources for hope.

410
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:44,260
 Haven't we?

411
00:17:44,260 --> 00:17:46,900
 In fact, I'm convinced.

412
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:53,000
 I'm convinced that many of us feel hopeless

413
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:59,080
 because we have hoped in less than the God of hope.

414
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:05,920
 Hope is the result of trusting in God.

415
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:09,320
 And yet we have trusted in so many other things

416
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:13,560
 and it's crippling our hope and it's crippling our health.

417
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:18,080
 The CDC released some data in 2023 that was pretty alarming.

418
00:18:18,080 --> 00:18:20,700
 Stated that 40% of American teenagers

419
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:25,040
 reported persistent feelings of sadness or hopelessness.

420
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:30,780
 And I would suggest that many of them

421
00:18:30,780 --> 00:18:33,440
 and many of us feel hopeless

422
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:36,600
 because we have settled for hoping in less

423
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,280
 than the God of hope.

424
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:40,040
 And we see this all throughout the scripture.

425
00:18:40,040 --> 00:18:41,380
 You see it in the Old Testament.

426
00:18:41,380 --> 00:18:43,160
 Jeremiah, known as the weeping prophet,

427
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:46,480
 in Jeremiah chapter two, verses 11 through 13, it says,

428
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:50,160
 "Has a nation ever changed its gods, little G?

429
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:52,000
 "Yet they are not gods at all.

430
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,360
 "But my people have exchanged their glorious God

431
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:56,480
 "for worthless idols."

432
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:58,160
 He says, "Be appalled at this, you heavens,

433
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:01,000
 "and shudder with great horror, declares the Lord.

434
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,600
 "My people have committed two sins.

435
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:07,080
 "They have forsaken me, the spring of living water,

436
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:11,060
 "and they have dug for themselves their own cisterns,

437
00:19:11,060 --> 00:19:15,080
 "broken cisterns that cannot hold water."

438
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:17,640
 So I want you to see the picture of what's happening here.

439
00:19:17,640 --> 00:19:22,640
 A cistern was like this man-made,

440
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:27,760
 pear-shaped, normally, deep hole with plaster.

441
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:30,480
 And it would be like cut down into the rocks,

442
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:32,680
 either in a community or sometimes

443
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:36,160
 in a wealthy family right outside of their home.

444
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:39,180
 And it was used to store water from the rain.

445
00:19:39,180 --> 00:19:42,280
 And so what the people were doing,

446
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:45,880
 the people that had depended on God time and time again,

447
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:48,560
 year after year after year, he would bring the rain,

448
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:51,440
 which was a sign of blessing, and provide for his people.

449
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,400
 And yet at some point, the people said,

450
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,300
 "You know what?

451
00:19:54,300 --> 00:20:00,280
 "Let's dig a hole, and let's put some plaster in it,

452
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:04,500
 "and let's store up the rainwater, just in case.

453
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:08,640
 "Just in case the rain cuts off tomorrow,

454
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:12,140
 "we will have saved up enough for ourselves today.

455
00:20:12,140 --> 00:20:16,260
 "Let's just have a backup plan.

456
00:20:16,260 --> 00:20:18,240
 "We'll still believe in God.

457
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:20,960
 "We'll still trust him for the rain.

458
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:23,560
 "But just so we have a plan B,

459
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:27,360
 "let's build a cistern out back."

460
00:20:29,940 --> 00:20:31,140
 I know what that's like.

461
00:20:31,140 --> 00:20:34,540
 I would guess many of you know what that's like.

462
00:20:34,540 --> 00:20:38,360
 I know when to raise my hands in worship,

463
00:20:38,360 --> 00:20:39,340
 when to pat my chest.

464
00:20:39,340 --> 00:20:40,600
 I know how to sing all the songs.

465
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:42,040
 I know my scripture.

466
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:43,960
 I'm in church every time the doors are open.

467
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,420
 I know how to do all the Christian thing.

468
00:20:45,420 --> 00:20:48,680
 I would pass the multiple choice test at heaven's gates

469
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:49,880
 if there were to be one.

470
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:53,000
 And yet functionally in my life,

471
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:57,060
 God exists to save me where my plan's not to work out.

472
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,380
 And that led me,

473
00:21:00,380 --> 00:21:02,960
 and that leads everybody who lives that way,

474
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:05,920
 into hopelessness.

475
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:11,940
 Israel rejected God from whom water had always flowed,

476
00:21:11,940 --> 00:21:17,420
 and they sought to replace God with cracked,

477
00:21:17,420 --> 00:21:21,960
 leaky cisterns, which would always be empty.

478
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:26,900
 They trusted in themselves instead of God,

479
00:21:26,900 --> 00:21:29,840
 and they faded into hopelessness

480
00:21:29,840 --> 00:21:33,320
 because what they built with their hands

481
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:35,800
 could never provide for what they longed for

482
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:37,620
 in their hearts.

483
00:21:37,620 --> 00:21:42,620
 Misplaced trust produces fragile hope.

484
00:21:42,620 --> 00:21:48,520
 And many of us know that.

485
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:51,180
 And all throughout the Psalms, you see this same picture.

486
00:21:51,180 --> 00:21:54,240
 Like in Psalm 33, this is an amazing Psalm.

487
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:57,560
 It says, "Blessed is the nation whose God is the Lord,

488
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:59,400
 the people he chose for his inheritance.

489
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:02,720
 From heaven, the Lord looks down and sees all mankind."

490
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:03,940
 That's pretty crazy to think about.

491
00:22:03,940 --> 00:22:06,940
 "From his dwelling place, he watches all who live on earth.

492
00:22:06,940 --> 00:22:09,700
 He who forms the hearts of all,

493
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:12,600
 who considers everything that they do."

494
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:13,620
 Look at the next verse.

495
00:22:13,620 --> 00:22:17,040
 "No king is saved by the size of his army,

496
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:20,420
 and no warrior escapes by his great strength.

497
00:22:20,420 --> 00:22:22,460
 A horse," look at these words,

498
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:26,660
 "A horse is a vain hope for deliverance.

499
00:22:26,660 --> 00:22:29,860
 Despite all its great strength, it cannot save.

500
00:22:29,860 --> 00:22:32,620
 But the eyes of the Lord are on those who fear him,

501
00:22:32,620 --> 00:22:36,700
 on those whose hope is in his unfailing love,

502
00:22:36,700 --> 00:22:39,420
 to deliver them from death and keep them alive in famine."

503
00:22:39,420 --> 00:22:43,700
 Verse 20, "We wait in hope for the Lord.

504
00:22:43,700 --> 00:22:46,260
 He is our help and he is our shield.

505
00:22:46,260 --> 00:22:51,260
 In him, our hearts rejoice, for we trust in his holy name.

506
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:55,820
 May your unfailing love be with us, Lord,

507
00:22:55,820 --> 00:23:00,180
 even as we put our hope in you."

508
00:23:00,180 --> 00:23:01,580
 Do you see it?

509
00:23:01,580 --> 00:23:03,860
 Another Psalm 20, verse seven.

510
00:23:03,860 --> 00:23:08,800
 "Some trust in chariots and some trust in horses,

511
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:13,800
 but we trust in the name of the Lord, our God."

512
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:17,780
 In many more Psalms, you see this picture

513
00:23:17,780 --> 00:23:19,100
 that there was a group of people

514
00:23:19,100 --> 00:23:22,020
 who trusted in horses and chariots,

515
00:23:22,020 --> 00:23:23,480
 in the strength of their horse.

516
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:25,560
 And you're like, "What is all that about?

517
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:26,980
 What's the big deal with the horses?"

518
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:30,620
 Well, in this day, horses represented strength,

519
00:23:30,620 --> 00:23:34,240
 status, prestige.

520
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:37,980
 They were the most feared military instrument of the day.

521
00:23:37,980 --> 00:23:40,380
 They represented victory.

522
00:23:40,380 --> 00:23:46,420
 And many people were tempted to trust in them.

523
00:23:46,420 --> 00:23:49,060
 And yet Psalm 33, 16 says,

