 Where you go, man, when's the last time you were reading it

781
00:36:37,120 --> 00:36:39,160
 and you had to put it down and you got to go,

782
00:36:39,160 --> 00:36:41,960
 oh wow, I got to make a change in my life.

783
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:44,000
 Oh wow, I got to text that person and apologize.

784
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:46,360
 Oh wow, I got to make this situation right over here.

785
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:48,320
 Oh wow, I got to write a letter to that person.

786
00:36:48,320 --> 00:36:50,920
 We have to feast on this word

787
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:54,000
 if we want fuel for the difficulties of life.

788
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,280
 And I want that for you.

789
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:58,240
 My life changed, not just because I got into the walls

790
00:36:58,240 --> 00:37:00,080
 of the church, though yes, that's amazing

791
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:01,960
 and we're all called to be in the walls of the church,

792
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:05,280
 but when I began to crave this word,

793
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:07,200
 and the same thing will happen for you.

794
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:11,100
 If you're hopeless today, I think the best action step

795
00:37:11,100 --> 00:37:15,840
 you could put in place tomorrow is to feast on this word.

796
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:19,920
 And as you do, you will find your discouraged heart

797
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:23,520
 starting to beat and lift up off the ground again.

798
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:25,780
 What a gift that we hold this in our hands.

799
00:37:25,780 --> 00:37:29,720
 Back to Jeremiah in Lamentations,

800
00:37:29,720 --> 00:37:33,720
 we said earlier that he is the weeping prophet.

801
00:37:33,720 --> 00:37:35,880
 In Lamentations 3, you don't have to go there,

802
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:37,480
 I'm just gonna mention a few things.

803
00:37:37,480 --> 00:37:39,360
 He's in a tough spot.

804
00:37:39,360 --> 00:37:41,660
 In the first few verses, the first 17 verses,

805
00:37:41,660 --> 00:37:43,000
 he says things like this.

806
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,800
 Verse number one, I am a man who has seen affliction.

807
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:50,600
 Verse number five, besieged and surrounded

808
00:37:50,600 --> 00:37:52,320
 with bitterness and hardship.

809
00:37:53,280 --> 00:37:57,920
 Verse 16, this one really makes my hair on my neck stand up.

810
00:37:57,920 --> 00:38:00,660
 He has ground my teeth like gravel.

811
00:38:00,660 --> 00:38:04,360
 He has robbed me of peace

812
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:07,260
 and I have forgotten what prosperity is.

813
00:38:07,260 --> 00:38:09,960
 This guy is in a tough spot.

814
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:13,520
 It is bleak, it looks hopeless.

815
00:38:13,520 --> 00:38:17,080
 But look what he does next in verses 21 through 24.

816
00:38:17,080 --> 00:38:18,960
 He says in the middle of all the fog,

817
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:20,720
 in the middle of all the bleakness,

818
00:38:20,720 --> 00:38:22,660
 in the middle of the hardship and difficulties

819
00:38:22,660 --> 00:38:25,400
 where my teeth feel like they've been ground into gravel

820
00:38:25,400 --> 00:38:27,480
 because life has kicked me so hard.

821
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:31,000
 He says, but this I call to mind

822
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:36,000
 and therefore I have hope.

823
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:39,600
 My man's got grounded teeth like gravel

824
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:42,000
 and he still has hope.

825
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:43,440
 And what does he call to mind?

826
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:45,920
 He said, the steadfast love of the Lord never ceases.

827
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:47,740
 His mercies never come to an end.

828
00:38:47,740 --> 00:38:49,120
 They are new every single morning.

829
00:38:49,120 --> 00:38:50,080
 Great is your faithfulness.

830
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:51,360
 The Lord is my portion.

831
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,720
 Save my soul.

832
00:38:52,720 --> 00:38:57,440
 Therefore I will hope in him.

833
00:38:57,440 --> 00:39:00,360
 What a powerful picture.

834
00:39:00,360 --> 00:39:05,360
 Suffering can only steal from you false or vain hopes.

835
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:11,800
 It cannot take from you true and eternal hope.

836
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,320
 In fact, in my own life, if I can be honest,

837
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:17,520
 when suffering and circumstances I didn't want

838
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:20,840
 came into my life, it only galvanized the hope

839
00:39:20,840 --> 00:39:22,360
 I have in Christ.

840
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:24,000
 Because I know one day he's coming

841
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:27,600
 and one day he's gonna make all of this right.

842
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:31,480
 So as we look to him as the source of hope,

843
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:34,760
 we sink our roots deep down into the soil

844
00:39:34,760 --> 00:39:39,760
 of the love of God and he supplies us with hope.

845
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:43,320
 He is the source and he is the supplier.

846
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:46,600
 Number three, God's hope, last one,

847
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:51,560
 God's hope not only endures, it abounds.

848
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:54,200
 Like the text gets crazier.

849
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:57,000
 The God of hope, may the God of hope fill you

850
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:59,520
 with all joy and peace in believing

851
00:39:59,520 --> 00:40:03,320
 or as you trust in him so that by the power of the spirit,

852
00:40:03,320 --> 00:40:08,320
 you may abound or overflow with hope.

853
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:14,480
 This word is translated in the NIV as overflow

854
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:16,560
 or in the ESV as abound.

855
00:40:16,560 --> 00:40:20,120
 It is the word perisseo and it's a pretty awesome word.

856
00:40:20,120 --> 00:40:22,560
 It's the same word used in the accounts

857
00:40:22,560 --> 00:40:25,880
 of the feeding of the 5,000 like in Matthew 14.

858
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:28,840
 You know the story, the little boy brings his Hebrew

859
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:31,240
 lunchable, two fish, five loaves of bread.

860
00:40:31,240 --> 00:40:34,080
 Jesus prays, multiplies it, feeds.

861
00:40:34,080 --> 00:40:36,800
 We oftentimes think just 5,000, but that's just the men.

862
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:38,200
 It doesn't include women and children.

863
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:41,920
 So it's at least 15,000, probably more than that.

864
00:40:41,920 --> 00:40:44,160
 He feeds them all.

865
00:40:44,160 --> 00:40:47,800
 And then look what it says in Matthew 14, 20.

866
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:52,000
 They all ate and were satisfied.

867
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:56,960
 And the disciples picked up 12 basketfuls

868
00:40:56,960 --> 00:41:01,000
 of broken pieces that were left over.

869
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:07,120
 Takes a lunchable, feeds 15,000 people.

870
00:41:07,120 --> 00:41:08,920
 The disciples are walking around.

871
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:11,520
 Everybody has stuff they can't eat anymore.

872
00:41:11,520 --> 00:41:14,200
 And it says that they walk around

873
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:19,200
 and they pick up 12 baskets that were perisseo.

874
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:21,560
 They were left over.

875
00:41:21,560 --> 00:41:23,260
 They were a ridiculous amount.

876
00:41:23,260 --> 00:41:24,200
 They were too much.

877
00:41:24,200 --> 00:41:25,480
 They were hard to comprehend.

878
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:27,400
 Too many, they were overflowing.

879
00:41:27,400 --> 00:41:29,920
 They abounded with food.

880
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,040
 That's the picture.

881
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:32,800
 That's what this word means.

882
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:36,720
 It's extra, it's abundant, it's overflowing.

883
00:41:38,080 --> 00:41:39,520
 And that's the kind of hope

884
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:42,480
 we as the people of God have access to.

885
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:45,840
 And I would guess you've probably seen that

886
00:41:45,840 --> 00:41:48,020
 at some point in your life.

887
00:41:48,020 --> 00:41:49,820
 Like, have you ever seen somebody

888
00:41:49,820 --> 00:41:52,800
 or do you have a friend or a parent or a grandmother

889
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:55,520
 that overflowed constantly with hope?

890
00:41:55,520 --> 00:42:01,960
 I have a friend named Maya Handler,

891
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:03,640
 is the picture over here.

892
00:42:03,640 --> 00:42:06,520
 When I was a student pastor of our church,

893
00:42:06,520 --> 00:42:10,120
 Maya was 14 years old and she was diagnosed

894
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:13,680
 with a very rare, aggressive and terrible form of cancer

895
00:42:13,680 --> 00:42:15,940
 called rhabdomyosarcoma.

896
00:42:15,940 --> 00:42:19,540
 And things, it was awful.

897
00:42:19,540 --> 00:42:24,720
 Things accelerated seemingly overnight.

898
00:42:24,720 --> 00:42:28,480
 And I can remember so many times,

899
00:42:28,480 --> 00:42:30,120
 I was a young student pastor.

900
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:32,000
 I still don't know what I'm doing,

901
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:34,120
 but I really didn't know what I was doing then.

902
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:37,320
 And I can remember pulling into the parking deck

903
00:42:37,320 --> 00:42:38,800
 at Children's Healthcare in Atlanta,

904
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:41,320
 the cancer hospital in Atlanta.

905
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:43,680
 And I remember sitting in the parking deck.

906
00:42:43,680 --> 00:42:45,680
 I would have my Bible open in my lap,

907
00:42:45,680 --> 00:42:51,000
 tears just dripping onto pages and I would plead with God.

908
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:53,300
 And I would say, God, give me something.

909
00:42:53,300 --> 00:42:56,520
 Give me a verse, give me a prayer,

910
00:42:56,520 --> 00:42:59,240
 give me something that I can walk into this room

911
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:02,440
 and encourage this 14 year old girl with.

912
00:43:02,440 --> 00:43:03,600
 Just give me something.

913
00:43:04,520 --> 00:43:07,840
 And at some point I'd close my Bible

914
00:43:07,840 --> 00:43:10,520
 and I'd get out of the car and I'd make it up

915
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:12,960
 to the cancer floor at this hospital.

916
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:16,080
 And I'd walk down the long, cold hallway into Maya's room.

917
00:43:16,080 --> 00:43:19,320
 And not one time, it never failed.

918
00:43:19,320 --> 00:43:21,680
 I would walk into her room and immediately

919
00:43:21,680 --> 00:43:23,160
 when the door opened, she would say,

920
00:43:23,160 --> 00:43:25,760
 Grant, you're never gonna believe what I read today.

921
00:43:25,760 --> 00:43:29,360
 You're never gonna believe this new song I heard.

922
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:30,640
 And then she would take out her Bible

923
00:43:30,640 --> 00:43:33,580
 and she'd have 50 different colors circling stuff

924
00:43:33,580 --> 00:43:36,800
 in her Bible and she was so eager to tell me

925
00:43:36,800 --> 00:43:38,800
 about how good God was.

926
00:43:38,800 --> 00:43:41,680
 And I remember thinking in my head,

927
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:43,240
 honestly, I really remember this.

928
00:43:43,240 --> 00:43:46,800
 I was like, man, maybe she doesn't know how bad it is.

929
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:50,520
 Like maybe her parents just didn't tell her

930
00:43:50,520 --> 00:43:54,140
 or maybe she's too young to really comprehend

931
00:43:54,140 --> 00:43:56,640
 that she has days or weeks left.

932
00:43:56,640 --> 00:44:02,160
 And every time I walked in, I mean ear to ear.

933
00:44:03,260 --> 00:44:05,840
 She lost her hair and her smile got bigger.

934
00:44:05,840 --> 00:44:08,660
 She got to a point where she couldn't stand up

935
00:44:08,660 --> 00:44:10,720
 to go walk to the restroom anymore.

936
00:44:10,720 --> 00:44:14,640
 And the joy became more and more loud out of her room.

937
00:44:14,640 --> 00:44:18,320
 She would have to do these MRI scans of her head

938
00:44:18,320 --> 00:44:19,640
 and they would put her in this thing

939
00:44:19,640 --> 00:44:22,120
 and they would ask her what music she would wanna play.

940
00:44:22,120 --> 00:44:23,960
 And she would wanna play worship music

941
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:25,800
 and she would insist that they turn it up

942
00:44:25,800 --> 00:44:27,080
 as loud as it could go.

943
00:44:27,080 --> 00:44:29,120
 And you'd be outside in the hallway

944
00:44:29,120 --> 00:44:30,880
 and you'd hear worship music going.

945
00:44:32,660 --> 00:44:35,280
 And I can remember thinking, walking into a room,

946
00:44:35,280 --> 00:44:39,320
 I'd be like, I'm supposed to be here encouraging you.

947
00:44:39,320 --> 00:44:42,460
 I'm not good at my job.

948
00:44:42,460 --> 00:44:45,680
 I'm supposed to be in here encouraging you.

949
00:44:45,680 --> 00:44:48,080
 I'm supposed to be transferring hope to you.

950
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:51,040
 And every single time I never even got a word in.

951
00:44:51,040 --> 00:44:55,240
 And at first I thought,

952
00:44:55,240 --> 00:44:57,960
 maybe she just doesn't understand it.

953
00:44:57,960 --> 00:44:59,960
 And then I remember when it clicked for me,

954
00:44:59,960 --> 00:45:01,560
 I went, oh no, I get it.

955
00:45:01,560 --> 00:45:04,860
 She has tapped into the God of hope

956
00:45:04,860 --> 00:45:08,580
 who has filled her with all joy and peace in believing

957
00:45:08,580 --> 00:45:12,380
 as she trusts in him so that by the power of the Holy Spirit

958
00:45:12,380 --> 00:45:17,380
 even in a cancer ward, she could overflow with hope.

959
00:45:17,380 --> 00:45:22,260
 This is the picture for us.

960
00:45:22,260 --> 00:45:28,220
 Life is hard, but God is good.

961
00:45:29,340 --> 00:45:34,340
 And we have a hope that transcends this world.

962
00:45:34,340 --> 00:45:37,180
 Maya went home to be with Jesus

963
00:45:37,180 --> 00:45:39,460
 and I can remember people saying to me,

964
00:45:39,460 --> 00:45:41,660
 and they didn't mean anything by it,

965
00:45:41,660 --> 00:45:43,860
 but I can remember people saying to me,

966
00:45:43,860 --> 00:45:47,600
 like, I'm so sorry that it didn't work out for her.

967
00:45:47,600 --> 00:45:50,060
 I'm so sorry that what we prayed for didn't really.

968
00:45:50,060 --> 00:45:52,420
 And I wanted to say back to everybody lovingly,

969
00:45:52,420 --> 00:45:56,500
 like she got exactly what she was hoping for.

970
00:45:56,500 --> 00:45:59,980
 Not only did her hope not disappoint,

971
00:45:59,980 --> 00:46:02,780
 her hope paled in comparison

972
00:46:02,780 --> 00:46:06,500
 when she met the one she loved most face to face

973
00:46:06,500 --> 00:46:08,720
 and went to a place cancer can't go.

974
00:46:08,720 --> 00:46:12,420
 Her hope did not get,

975
00:46:12,420 --> 00:46:14,820
 she didn't get her hopes up to be disappointed.

976
00:46:14,820 --> 00:46:18,260
 Her hope will last and echo for eternity.

977
00:46:18,260 --> 00:46:22,100
 And I don't know what you're up against in life right now.

978
00:46:22,100 --> 00:46:26,100
 I don't know why your soul feels like

979
00:46:26,100 --> 00:46:28,660
 it's just bottoming out right now.

980
00:46:28,660 --> 00:46:30,460
 I don't know what circumstances,

981
00:46:30,460 --> 00:46:31,440
 I don't know what hardships,

982
00:46:31,440 --> 00:46:32,980
 I don't know what difficulty you're facing.

983
00:46:32,980 --> 00:46:36,140
 I don't know what kind of discouragement you're up against.

984
00:46:36,140 --> 00:46:37,740
 I don't know what's causing you to think,

985
00:46:37,740 --> 00:46:39,740
 maybe I should just cash all this in.

986
00:46:39,740 --> 00:46:43,100
 I don't know what lies the enemy's whispering over you.

987
00:46:43,100 --> 00:46:46,620
 I don't know what's causing you to feel hopeless.

988
00:46:46,620 --> 00:46:51,060
 But I came here tonight to say there is a person,

989
00:46:51,060 --> 00:46:52,740
 you can put your trust in him.

990
00:46:52,740 --> 00:46:54,540
 And as you put your trust in him,

991
00:46:54,540 --> 00:46:57,980
 you will get a hope that is gritty and durable

992
00:46:57,980 --> 00:47:01,260
 and dependable and will last for all of eternity.

993
00:47:01,260 --> 00:47:04,020
 And even in the most difficult days of life,

994
00:47:04,020 --> 00:47:06,460
 you can worship your way through.

995
00:47:06,460 --> 00:47:10,500
 You can overflow with hope.

996
00:47:10,500 --> 00:47:13,740
 So for the people in the room today,

997
00:47:13,740 --> 00:47:17,820
 if you're alive in Jesus, if you belong to the King,

998
00:47:17,820 --> 00:47:20,540
 I came on the authority of God's word today

999
00:47:20,540 --> 00:47:25,540
 to tell you you should get your hopes up.

1000
00:47:25,540 --> 00:47:27,500
 Let's pray together.

